name: HsnUltrasoundDICOM
author: hansono
description:
A library to send ultrasound images to a DICOM supported server or query patients/studies.
Imebra DICOM Library was used internally.

childs.name: Storage
childs.description:
This service queues ultrasound images from applications using the DICOM module and sends them.
The progress of image transfer can be monitored by the application through registered callbacks.
Because image transmission is asynchronous, other threads can stop the transmission depending on the situation.

childs.name: enqueue
childs.description: Enqueue the images to be sent

parameters.name: server
parameters.description: The configuration of the server to which user want to send images

parameters.name: images
parameters.description: ultrasound images to put in the queue

childs.name: getQueue
childs.description: Get the remaining images in the image queue.

childs.name: send
childs.description:
Send the images in the image queue from another thread.
This operation can be canceled while it is in progress.

parameters.name: isSync
parameters.description: If this parameter is set to true, this function waits for the current image transmission to finish.

childs.name: pause
childs.description: Stop the image transfer operation in progress in another thread.

childs.name: clear
childs.description: Clear all images in the image queue.

childs.name: registerProgressCallback
childs.description: Clear all images in the image queue.

parameters.name: callback
parameters.description: Callback that informs image transfer progress.
